	Commenta Hollander: "There is a continuing debate (if not one of
particular consequence) about the precise meaning of this 'water.' Some
take it in the wider sense, i.e., Christians are warned not to take
vows lightly in the hopes that they will 'cleanse' them of guilt; others
stay closer to the literal, seeing in ^acqua~ the cleansing holy water
of easy absolution granted by an all-too-human priestly intercessor
